*About Me*\n

Welcome to my homepage!

I’m Jichu Li, currently an undergraduate student in the Honors Talent Program in Statistics and Data Science at [https://www.ruc.edu.cn/ Renmin University of China]. I'm also a visiting student at [https://www.ttic.edu/ Toyota Technological Institute at Chicago], hosted by [https://zhiyuanli.ttic.edu/ Prof. Zhiyuan Li]. 
During my research journey, I had the fortune to work with [https://difanzou.github.io/ Prof. Difan Zou] on learning theory at The University of Hong Kong and [https://zhoufeng6288.github.io/index.html Prof. Feng Zhou] on multimodal time-series modeling at Renmin University of China.

*Research Interests*\n
My research interests lie at the intersection of machine learning theory and optimization. I am dedicated to building a rigorous theoretical understanding of modern optimization algorithms in deep learning, analyzing their convergence, implicit bias, and generalization. 
At the same time, I am interested in applying these theoretical insights to the design and analysis of large language models (LLMs/MLLMs), including LLM-based approaches for modeling complex sequential and event-based data.

Feel free to email me if you’d like to connect!

